      "message": "Done, both parts.\n\n1. cue mod publish now prints a note when cue.mod/local-module.cue is present:\n\n\tnote: cue.mod/local-module.cue is not published; it only affects local development\n\nI went with the note rather than a --without-local flag, which as you say would get annoying. To make the note literally true I also made modzip omit cue.mod/local-module.cue from the published zip (it was previously being packed verbatim, like any other file under cue.mod), alongside the existing .hg_archival.txt-style omissions.\n\n2. Publishing now enforces that a full tidy is happy first. cue mod publish runs the full two-file CheckTidy (informed by local-module.cue, with directory replaces resolved), so a stale module.cue is rejected with \"module is not tidy, use \u0027cue mod tidy\u0027\". To make that meaningful I had to strengthen CheckTidy itself: it previously only checked that each view was internally tidy, which missed exactly your case (module.cue advertising a lower version than local-module.cue selects). It now also checks that module.cue already carries the maximum version across both views, so cue mod tidy --check catches it too. New tests cover both the success and the stale-rejection paths.",
